                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 774/393.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Vignaud</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-11-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 4, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 528.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that Mr. Pichon has
                    just notified this embassy of the appointment of the three French delegates to
                    the opium conference. They are: M. L. O. Ratard, consul general of France at
                    Shanghai; Mr. Brenier, under director of the department of agriculture, forests,
                    and commerce of Indo-China; and M. Cronillon, inspector of first grade of the
                    customhouse service of Indo-China.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry Vignaud.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
